docs.lead_paragraph: COLLEGES TOP PROSPECT WILL SIGN WITH FLORIDA -- Jai Lucas, a McDonald's all-American and son of the former N.B.A. player and coach John Lucas, said yesterday that he would sign a letter of intent to play basketball for Florida. Lucas picked Florida over Kentucky and Oklahoma State. He made the announcement at his high school in Bellaire, Tex. A 5-foot-10 guard, Lucas averaged 25 points and 6 assists as a senior. CLEMSON DROPPED PREGNANCY POLICY -- The Clemson athletic director, Terry Don Phillips, said yesterday in a statement posted on the athletic department Web site that the track coach Marcia Noad had presented her team with written rules, which included the line, ''Pregnancy resulting in the inability to compete and positively contribute to the program's success will result in the modification of your grant-in-aid money.''
